  "prompt": "What percentage of commission do sellers need to pay e-commerce websites like Flipkart, eBay, Amazon, Shopclues, Shimply, Myntra etc., when selling clothing such as t-shirts?",
  "response": "The commission rates that e-commerce platforms charge sellers can vary based on factors such as product category, seller status, and specific platform policies. Below is an overview of the typical commission percentages for selling clothing items like t-shirts on major e-commerce websites as of 2023:\n\n### **1. Amazon**\n- **Commission Rate:** Approximately **15-17%**\n- **Details:** Amazon charges a referral fee based on the product category. For apparel and accessories, the fee is generally around 17%. Additional fees may apply if you use services like Fulfillment by Amazon (FBA).\n\n### **2. Flipkart**\n- **Commission Rate:** Approximately **12-15%**\n- **Details:** Flipkart's commission for apparel items like t-shirts typically falls within this range. The exact percentage can depend on factors such as brand exclusivity and seller performance.\n\n### **3. eBay**\n- **Commission Rate:** Approximately **10%**\n- **Details:** eBay charges a final value fee based on the total sale amount, including shipping. For most categories, including clothing, the fee is around 10%.\n\n### **4. Myntra**\n- **Commission Rate:** Approximately **10-18%**\n- **Details:** As a fashion-centric platform in India, Myntra's commission varies based on the brand and product specifics. Established brands might incur higher fees compared to emerging sellers.\n\n### **5. ShopClues**\n- **Commission Rate:** Approximately **10-12%**\n- **Details:** ShopClues generally offers competitive commission rates for apparel, making it an attractive option for sellers looking to minimize fees.\n\n### **6. Shopify**\n- **Commission Structure:** \n  - **Subscription Fees:** Starts at ~$29/month for the basic plan.\n  - **Transaction Fees:** **2.9% + 30\u00a2** per transaction if using Shopify Payments. Additional fees may apply if using third-party payment gateways.\n- **Details:** Unlike traditional marketplaces, Shopify is a platform for building your own online store. The costs include monthly subscriptions and transaction fees, but you retain more control over your branding and customer experience.\n\n### **Additional Considerations**\n- **Promotional Fees:** Some platforms offer promotional services or premium listings at additional costs.\n- **Shipping Fees:** Depending on the platform and fulfillment methods used, shipping fees may be separate from commission charges.\n- **Volume Discounts:** High-volume sellers might negotiate lower commission rates or receive discounts based on their sales performance.\n\n### **Conclusion**\nCommission rates are subject to change and can vary based on specific agreements or changes in platform policies. It's essential to review the latest terms and conditions on each platform's official website or consult with their seller support teams to get the most accurate and up-to-date information.\n\nIf you're planning to sell on multiple platforms, consider the overall cost structure, including commissions, subscription fees, shipping, and other ancillary costs, to determine which marketplace aligns best with your business model and profit margins.",
